Package eu.kartoffelquadrat.maxplayercolours

Class PlayerColourUtils

java.lang.Object
eu.kartoffelquadrat.maxplayercolours.PlayerColourUtils
public class PlayerColourUtils
extends java.lang.Object
Helper class to create human distinguishable set of colours. Generated colours have maximized saturation and value in HSV room. The produces colours have maximized hue distance in HSB room.
Author:
Maximilian Schiedermeier

  • Method Details

    • generateColourSet

      public static int[][] generateColourSet​(int originR, int originG, int originB, int targetArraySize) throws PlayerColourUtilsException
      Produces an array of n sRGB colours, based on a single origin sRGB colour. The origin colour will be maximized in HSV saturation. All produced colours have also maximized HSB saturation and have a mutually maximized hue distance.
      Parameters:
      originR - int value for origin colour Red channel. Must be in range 0-255.
      originG - int value for origin colour Green channel. Must be in range 0-255.
      originB - int value for origin colour Blue channel. Must be in range 0-255.
      targetArraySize - int value to specify the amount of desired colours in the target colour array.
      Returns:
      2D-color array of size @{setSize}. Produces values are RGB triplets in sRGB space. First position represents the max-saturated equivalent of the origin.
      Throws:
      PlayerColourUtilsException - if a provided colour channel is out of range, the channels add up to a greyscale colour, or the target array size is not in valid range [2-8]

    • generateMaxDistanceSet

      private static int[][] generateMaxDistanceSet​(float originHue, int targetArraySize)
      Based on a single orig
      Parameters:
      originHue - as the hue serving as fixpoint for the rotation shift of all produced colours on the HSB hue circle.
      targetArraySize - as the amount of colours to produce (includes the origin).
      Returns:
      2D int array listing RGB triplets [0-255] per channel for all produced colours.

    • verifyIsValidNonGreyScaleSRGB

      private static void verifyIsValidNonGreyScaleSRGB​(int originR, int originG, int originB) throws PlayerColourUtilsException
      Helper method to verify if provided rgb channel values are allowed sRGB space. Greyscale input values are not allowed, for their saturation can not be maximized.
      Parameters:
      originR - int value for origin colour Red channel. Must be in range 0-255.
      originG - int value for origin colour Green channel. Must be in range 0-255.
      originB - int value for origin colour Blue channel. Must be in range 0-255.
      Throws:
      PlayerColourUtilsException - in case the provided origin RGB represents a colour without hue (a greyscale colour).

    • isValidChannelValue

      private static boolean isValidChannelValue​(int value)
      Verifies if provided value is in range [0-255]
      Parameters:
      value - as the number to test for target range.
      Returns:
      whether the provided value is in target range or not.

    • extractHue

      private static float extractHue​(int originR, int originG, int originB)
      Boosts colour saturation (input provided in sRGB room) to maximum and returns the resulting HSB-hue value.
      Parameters:
      originR - int value for origin colour Red channel. Must be in range 0-255.
      originG - int value for origin colour Green channel. Must be in range 0-255.
      originB - int value for origin colour Blue channel. Must be in range 0-255.
      Returns:
      float as target hue value in HSB room, if saturation and brightness of the provided sRBG input colour boosted to max.
